news.title: Over 560 building plans approved during Aug-Sept in Nashik
news.para: Nashik Municipal Corporation (NMC) has received 1,485 building plan proposals so far since April this financial year, including 871 proposals in just the August-September period.

news.title: Greater Noida authority to recover GST dues from allottees
news.para: Authority officials, however, clarified that residential allottees will not have to pay the tax for urban services as the GST Council considers the industrial authorities as civic bodies.

news.title: Only 32 properties sold in Chandigarh housing board auction
news.para: Even reduction in reserve prices failed to produce the desired effect during the auction. The board had reduced reserve price of commercial units on leasehold basis by 20% and residential units on leasehold basis by 10%.

news.title: Delhi: DPCC imposes Rs 90 lakh fine on construction sites so far
news.para: Environment minister Gopal Rai said, under the ongoing anti-dust campaign, DPCC teams had visited 1,105 construction sites.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: Construction sites to shut for a day
news.para: According to the complaint filed by the BAI, the builders had earlier expressed the inability to accept the demand of trade unions to hike the loading and unloading rates.

news.title: Over 500 buildings unstable, raze them in a week: Bengaluru civic body
news.para: Revenue minister R Ashoka had ordered BBMP chief commissioner Gaurav Gupta to conduct a special drive to inspect structurally unsafe buildings in the city.

news.title: Mumbai: Flamingo park's eco sensitive boundary shrinks to max four km
news.para: For the real estate industry, the notification would expedite obtaining development permissions in 15 civic wards from Chembur, Kurla, Bhandup, Mulund, Ghatkopar East to Kandivli, Borivli, Dahisar, Andheri East and Bandra East. Even areas in Dadar, Matunga and Parel which were impacted will be easier to construct.

news.title: Activists object to MahaRERA nod for Mistry Constructions' project in Navi Mumbai
news.para: Last month, MahaRera issued a registration certificate to a project called ‘Infinite Residency’ proposed by developer Mistry Constructions at Navi Mumbai.

news.title: Maharashtra hikes Gunthewari charges by three times, fixes premium for excess built-up
news.para: Now, owners of unauthorized layouts and plots will have to shell out Rs168 per sq ft as against existing Rs56 per sq ft. The state’s urban development department issued the notification on Monday increasing the charges.

news.title: Western Digital leases 6.8 lakh sq ft office space in Bengaluru
news.para: Bengaluru has recorded net absorption of about 1 million sq ft in July-September quarter. The city’s office market witnessed increased demand from co-working operators, accounting for about 48% of the leasing activity.

news.title: WeWork back to Wall Street, two years after fiasco
news.para: Shares of the new entity, which is worth about $9 billion, are expected to begin trading Thursday on the New York Stock Exchange under the ticker symbol "WE." The SPAC is a vehicle used just to raise capital and list shares without going through traditional initial public offering process.

news.title: Chinese property bonds firm after Kaisa and Sunac make coupon payments
news.para: Sunac China, which has a $27.14 million payment due Tuesday, has paid its bondholders, a source with direct knowledge of the matter said.

news.title: U.S. housing starts, permits tumble in September
news.para: Housing starts dropped 1.6% to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 1.555 million units last month, the Commerce Department said on Tuesday. Data for August was revised down to a rate of 1.580 million units from the previously reported 1.615 million units.

news.title: ACC's net profit increases 24% at Rs 450.21 crore in Q3 2021
news.para: The company's total income stood at Rs 3,812.31 crore in Q3 2021, a increase of 6 per cent from Rs 3,582.82 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: HeidelbergCement India's profit dips 4.55% to Rs 59.56 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: In a separate filing, HeidelbergCement India said its independent director/chairperson Akila Krishnakumar has resigned from the position and the board has accepted her resignation
